## Original Claim

A tradition's inquiry is shaped by its stopping rule: the moment a method tells the practitioner that the next move would distort rather than clarify. Advaita stops objectifying at the non-objectifiable knower. Early Buddhism stops granting ownership to any aggregate, state, or insight. Daoism stops when deliberate control reappears. Sufism stops when self-possession interrupts remembrance and love. Neoplatonism stops when attention scatters from unity into mere multiplicity. These rules make different silences feel final. They sit between instrument and inference: before a tradition argues what silence means, it has trained the practitioner where inquiry should cease, continue, or change form.

## Why It Might Be New

This adds a variable not covered by the current Lumenary models. The instrument problem asks how practice generates data. Inferential gap asks what conclusions are drawn. Alarm profile asks what error feels dangerous. Verification architecture asks who can certify success. Stopping rule asks where the method withdraws permission to keep using the same kind of inquiry. It explains why similar quieting or de-identification can harden into different claims without treating convergence as proof or disagreement as mere translation failure.

## Source Basis

- Thinking method source: notes/source-cards/daoism-dao-de-jing-chapter-48.md on learning by decrease and wu wei. I applied decrease by subtracting the urge to find one shared essence, then asking where each practice tells inquiry to change form.
- Method critique source: notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-mn-1-mulapariyaya-sutta.md on conceiving experience. It checked the Daoist lens by warning that even a clean stopping rule can become another thing the comparer owns.
- notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-brihadaranyaka-upanishad-3-7-23.md and notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-shankara-upadesa-sahasri.md as witness-side sources where the knower resists objectification.
- notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-59-anattalakkhana-sutta.md and notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-95-phenapindupama-sutta.md as sources where no aggregate is fit to be taken as self or final ground.
- notes/source-cards/daoism-zhuangzi.md as a Daoist source for fasting the heart-mind, self-forgetting, and non-ontological transformation.
- notes/source-cards/sufism-al-ghazali-the-alchemy-of-happiness.md as a relational source where self-knowledge, God-knowledge, remembrance, and love resist reduction to detached observation.
- notes/source-cards/neoplatonism-plotinus-enneads-fifth-ennead.md as a unity and return source where dispersion from the One frames the danger of multiplicity.
- Prior Codex findings: Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence, Negation Has An Address, Return Is the Audit, Each Path Has a Different Alarm, and The Comparison Has A Self.
