"High. The model imposes a modern reflexive category, method's relation to itself, on traditions that may speak instead of upaya, realization, grace, direct recognition, non-grasping, or annihilation of ego. It also risks treating stage-specific pedagogies as stable types.", "secondary_literature_gap": "I did not find an exact three-type typology of contemplative methods as confirming, canceling, and dissolving at completion. But the self-canceling portion has very strong prior art in Nagarjuna, Wittgenstein ladder readings, Buddhist raft discussions, and Sells on apophatic unsaying. The dissolving portion is also standard in fana, zuowang, and Dzogchen descriptions. The new part is the comparative axis and its predicted consequences, not the individual patterns.", "structural_observation": "The Mandukya and Heart Sutra contrast is promising but not clean. Mandukya verse 7 negates ordinary consciousness categories, then ends by saying this is Atman and is to be known, which supports a confirming limit move. Yet Shankara's commentary also says affirmative and negative language fail, so Mandukya contains a self-canceling linguistic element. The Heart Sutra negates aggregates, sense bases, ignorance, the four truths, wisdom, and attainment, which supports the self-canceling reading. Yet it immediately says bodhisattvas rely on Prajnaparamita and gives a mantra, so the method is retained as reliance and recitation, not simply canceled. The close read supports a two-axis model better than a pure three-box typology."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.64, "source_reliability": 0.78}, "run_ids": ["20260526-120003-codex-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c", "20260526-120003-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c"], "title": "The Method's Reckoning: What a Practice Does With Its Own Authority at Completion", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Smith on Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Sells on apophatic unsaying, or the ra